Greek name <i>Hagnē</i>, from the feminine form of the adjective <i>hagnos</i> ‘pure, holy’. This was the name of a young Roman virgin martyred in the persecutions instigated by the Roman emperor Diocletian in   ad  303 . She became a very popular saint in the Middle Ages. Her name was early associated with Latin <i>agnus</i> ‘lamb’, leading to the consistent dropping of the initial <i>H-</i> and to her representation in art accompanied by a lamb. The colloquial form <i>Annes</i> led to some confusion with <i>Ann(e)</i> in earlier centuries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Agnes Dickinson was born about 1340, in England, United Kingdom. She married William Wightman about 1354, in Leicestershire, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in her hometown."},"et":{"Abt 1340–":"umbes 1340–Surnud","1340–Male":"1340–Surnud","1380–1471":"1380–1471","1340–Female":"1340–Surnud","Abt 1340":"umbes 1340","1340":"1340","about 1354":"umbes 1354","1471":"1471","1380":"1380","Leicestershire, England":"Leicestershire, England","Burbage, Leicestershire, England":"Burbage, Leicestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1340–":"noin 1340–Kuollut","1340–Male":"1340–Kuollut","1380–1471":"1380–1471","1340–Female":"1340–Kuollut","Abt 1340":"noin 1340","1340":"1340","about 1354":"noin 1354","1471":"1471","1380":"1380","Leicestershire, England":"Leicestershire, England","Burbage, Leicestershire, England":"Burbage, Leicestershire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1340–":"environ 1340–Décédée","1340–Male":"1340–Décédé","1380–1471":"1380–1471","1340–Female":"1340–Décédée","Abt 1340":"environ 1340","1340":"1340","about 1354":"environ 1354","1471":"1471","1380":"1380","Leicestershire, England":"Leicestershire, Angleterre","Burbage, Leic